Firstly we need to determine how many bags of equal parts (for different uses) Heather would divide into since all three products take up part of one 'unit'. Assuming this unit means making something per every four portions(one fourth), We know that :  
Total Raisins / Portion size= Number of Batches or Units produced;   
So let’s calculate how large portion sizes could possibly work out without going over what was used:(the largest possible amount being divided evenly through these types of cooking needs). This allows us to solve for NxN matrix which provides maximum units.    
Maximum Unit Size=(Raisin Amount)/Four ;    
For Granola , Snack Mix & Cookies,(Each taking exactly same fraction)= Total Raisin Count/(Number Of Usages);     
Which here equals -> Maximum_Unit_Size = ((3rd Power)(Cookies)+Granola+snackmix))^((Set Up Matrix));      
Substituting numbers above yields->=>Maximum_Unit_Size=(6483268)÷[(Both Product Types)]^(Ways To Divide Them Equally As One Unit)^

